---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const blogContent = `
<p>A common pitfall in agentic systems is the assumption that large language models can autonomously achieve mathematical consistency through iterative prompting. In our experience, this approach is suboptimal. Bridging the gap between informal combinatorial reasoning and formal verification in Lean 4 requires a systematic reduction of probabilistic noise.</p>

<p>To address this, we have implemented an adversarial verification pipeline. This system anchors model generation to peer-reviewed literature and utilizes a multi-layered evaluation strategy to identify flaws in proposed hypotheses at the earliest possible stage of the search process.</p>

<p>The following execution trace illustrates the system's workflow when evaluating structural lower bounds for $R(4,6)$:</p>

<pre><code>// 1. Initial State: The Librarian queries the offline arXiv database for relevant literature.
[Librarian] Extracted arXiv query: "Find a structural lower bound for R(4,6) utilizing k-perturbed symmetric algebraic sets"
[Librarian] Top matches:
  1. "Multiplicative differential algebraic K-theory and applications" (arxiv:1311.1421v3)
  2. "How to show a set is not algebraic" (arxiv:math/0106084v1)
  3. "Elliptic curves and lower bounds for class numbers" (arxiv:2001.07332v3)

[Ideation] Selected Seed: "Elliptic curves and lower bounds for class numbers"
[Ideation] Strategy formulated: A structural lower bound for the Ramsey number R(4,6) can be established by perturbing a symmetric C...
[Validation] AST syntactically valid in Lean 4.

// 2. The Sandbox: The hypothesis is evaluated using Python-based probes and SMT solvers.
[Explorer] Probing domains: Algebraic Graph Theory, Computational Hypergraph Theory...
[Explorer] Synthesizing evidence...
[Explorer] Signal: COUNTER-EXAMPLE FOUND (2 counter-examples)
[Explorer] Result: The hypothesized bound failed.

// 3. Iterative Refinement: The system autonomously generates a revised hypothesis from alternative literature.
[Librarian] Extracted arXiv query: "Find a structural lower bound for R(4,6) utilizing k-perturbed symmetric algebraic sets"
...
[Ideation] Selected Seed: "On the Frobenius fields of abelian varieties over number fields"
[Ideation] Strategy formulated: A structural lower bound for R(4,6) can be established by an algebraic perturbation of the connectio...

// 4. Rate Limiting Resilience: The orchestration layer handles API capacity constraints.
[Ideation] API capacity limit detected. Retries remaining: 4. Pausing for 5 seconds...
[Ideation] Strategy formulated: A structural lower bound for R(4,6) can be established by an algebraic perturbation of the connectio...
[Validation] AST syntactically valid in Lean 4.
[Explorer] Probing domains: Algebraic Graph Theory, Number Theory...

// 5. Verification: The RedTeam agent utilizes Z3 to attempt falsification.
[RedTeam] Launching generative adversary against conjecture.
[RedTeam] Synthesizing Z3 validation script. Executing in sandbox...
  [SolverBridge] Executing python3 (timeout: 45000ms)
  [SolverBridge] python3 completed with exit code 1
[RedTeam] Sandbox execution complete. No counter-examples identified.

// 6. Formalization Challenge: Identifying syntax errors in Lean 4 synthesis.
[Sketcher] Drafting Lean 4 formalization for hypothesis...
[Sketcher] COMPILER TRACE:
&lt;stdin&gt;:7:32: error: invalid field 'IsPrime', the environment does not contain 'Nat.IsPrime'
&lt;stdin&gt;:23:2: error: invalid field 'cliqueNumber', the environment does not contain 'SimpleGraph.cliqueNumber'

[SketcherActor] ERROR: SketcherAgent failed to produce a valid Lean 4 skeleton after 3 attempts.</code></pre>

<p>This trace highlights several key components of our updated architecture.</p>

<h2>1. Literature-Grounded Ideation</h2>

<p>Before expanding nodes in the search tree, the <code>Librarian</code> agent executes a vector search against a local LanceDB instance containing arXiv metadata. This ensures that the <code>Ideation</code> process is rooted in established mathematical literature rather than relying solely on the model's pre-trained weights.</p>

<p>In the example above, the system initially utilized <em>Elliptic curves and lower bounds for class numbers</em> to inform its graph-theoretic bounds. When the resulting hypothesis was falsified, the system autonomously refined its query to select an alternative seed, <em>Frobenius fields of abelian varieties</em>, illustrating a literature-driven approach to hypothesis refinement.</p>

<h2>2. The Falsification Repository</h2>

<p>When the <code>Explorer</code> identifies a counter-example, the failure is recorded in a persistent state map. This prevents the system from re-evaluating identical or structurally similar topologies in subsequent iterations.</p>

<p>By offloading initial falsification to standard symbolic execution environments (e.g., Z3 running in a Python sandbox), we isolate the computationally intensive formal proof kernel from invalid conjectures. This multi-stage filtering process optimizes resource allocation by identifying flawed hypotheses early in the pipeline.</p>

<h2>3. Localized Tactic Routing</h2>

<p>To minimize latency during MCTS branch evaluation, we have replaced standard network-based API calls with local UNIX sockets for tactic communication. By streaming data directly to a local daemon, we have reduced the inference overhead from approximately 40ms to 1.2ms per call. This improvement is critical for maintaining high-throughput logic loops during deep tree searches.</p>

<h2>4. Operational Resilience</h2>

<p>The orchestration layer, built on XState, provides robust handling for external API constraints. When service interruptions or rate limits occur, the system transitions to a paused state and implements an exponential backoff strategy, ensuring that the execution context is preserved and operations resume automatically once services are restored.</p>

<h2>5. Syntax Verification Bottlenecks</h2>

<p>While the system has improved its ability to generate mathematically sound hypotheses, formalizing these results in Lean 4 remains a challenge. As shown in the trace, the <code>Sketcher</code> agent may still produce syntactically incorrect code, such as referencing non-existent Mathlib methods. Addressing these formalization gaps by enforcing stricter adherence to verified topological primitives is our current focus.</p>

<p>The progress achieved thus far is the result of rigorous state management, localized tactic routing, and a multi-layered verification strategy. We are continuing to refine these components to enhance the system's reliability and proof-discovery capabilities.</p>
`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Adversarial Trees and Polite Infrastructure — Blog" activeNav="blog">
  <article class="blog-post">
    <div class="container blog-container">
      <header class="post-header">
        <a href="/blog/" class="back-link">← Back to all posts</a>
        <div class="post-meta">
          <time>April 07, 2026</time>
          <span class="tag">architecture</span>
          <span class="tag">mcts</span>
          <span class="tag">rag</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="post-title">Adversarial Trees and Polite Infrastructure</h1>
        <p class="post-subtitle">Why we abandoned raw LLM generation in favor of Lakatosian feedback loops, local LanceDB vectors, and native UNIX sockets.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="post-content" set:html={blogContent} />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .blog-post {
    padding: 60px 0 100px;
  }

  .blog-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .post-header {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .post-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .post-meta time {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    background: var(--accent-purple-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-purple);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .post-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .post-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .post-content {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .post-content :global(h2) {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 48px 0 24px;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .post-content :global(h3) {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 32px 0 16px;
  }

  .post-content :global(p) {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .post-content :global(ul), .post-content :global(ol) {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    padding-left: 24px;
  }

  .post-content :global(li) {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .post-content :global(a) {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .post-content :global(a:hover) {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 4px;
  }

  .post-content :global(code) {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: var(--background-highlight);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--accent-green);
  }

  .post-content :global(pre) {
    background: var(--background-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  .post-content :global(pre code) {
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
    color: inherit;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .post-content :global(strong) {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .post-content :global(blockquote) {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 32px 0;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .blog-post { padding: 40px 0 80px; }
    .post-title { font-size: 2.2rem; }
    .post-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  }
</style>
